      "amount": "1 tablespoon",
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "name": "sriracha sauce",
      "amount": "2 teaspoons",
      "notes": "adjust to taste"
    },
    {
      "name": "salt",
      "amount": "1/4 teaspoon",
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "name": "black pepper",
      "amount": "1/4 teaspoon",
      "notes": ""
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 400°F (200°C).",
    "In a medium saucepan, whisk together beurre monte, unsweetened almond milk, and sriracha sauce. Bring to a simmer over medium heat, whisking constantly.",
    "In a large mixing bowl, combine shredded mexican cheese, flour, grated ginger, salt, and black pepper. Stir until well combined.",
    "Pour the beurre monte mixture over the cheese mixture and stir until smooth.",
    "Transfer the mixture to a 9x13 inch baking dish and top with caramelized shallots.",
    "Bake for 25-30 minutes, or until the casserole is golden brown and set.",
    "Remove from oven and let cool for 5 minutes before serving.",
    "Slice and serve hot."
  ],
